# Influential Observations

## Building the leverage-residuals plot

We need two quantities from `augment()`:

- `.hat`: the leverage of each observation — how far it sits in predictor space
- `.std.resid`: standardised residual — how unusual the outcome is given the predictors
- `.cooksd`: Cook's distance — the combined influence measure


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hotels_aug <- augment(model_work) |>
  bind_cols(hotels |> select(hotel_id, city))

threshold_cook <- 4 / nrow(hotels)
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
hotels_aug |>
  ggplot(aes(.hat, .std.resid,
             size  = .cooksd,
             color = .cooksd > threshold_cook)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.5) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = c(-2, 2), linetype = "dashed", color = "gray50") +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c("steelblue", "tomato"),
    labels = c("Below threshold", "Cook's D > 4/n"),
    name   = NULL
  ) +
  scale_size_continuous(guide = "none") +
  labs(
    x        = "Leverage (h_ii)",
    y        = "Standardised residuals",
    title    = "Influential observations",
    subtitle = "Points outside the ±2 band and/or with high Cook's D warrant investigation"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Leverage vs. standardised residuals. Size = Cook's distance. Red = above the 4/n threshold.](demo_files/figure-html/fig-leverage-manual-1.png){#fig-leverage-manual width=672}
:::
:::


